SUDO   full abrivation is "super user do" or "subtute user"
SUDO user can do anythig like he can change all permition as already given permission to existing users
and he can delete all files finally he is having overall permissions in server.

SUDO user can do normal user as a SUDO user by using visudo in ROOT

suppose user name is vinod
ex:adduser vinod

after that if we need to give all permissions like as a sudo

here " >> " means enter
sudo su >> visudo su

in visudo showing three catagories as am show in below 
1.all permissions {"here user can taking all permissions with password"}
2.group user {"in group"}
3.no password reqire {"any password require"}





